main event: A bright white unidentified flying object was observed in Alaska for 11 minutes on 16 June 1953.
interesting points: The object was seen heading north at an altitude of 13,500 feet., It changed colors from bright red to blue to bright white during the observation., The sighting lasted precisely from 2738Z to 2748Z Zulu time., There was no physical evidence found., The conclusion states there is insufficient data for evaluation.
